2.text: Add a little bit of green paint to make a deeper red.

3.text: Use an analogous shade of blue to make a red darker and muted.

4.text: Add black to change the shade of red and make it richer.

5.text: Combine red with a gray to make a darker, flat red.

6.text: Mix a red with a brown to make a muted, earthy shade of red.

7.text: Add another coat of the same red to make the color richer.

8.text: Apply a coat of maroon, burgundy or crimson to a lighter shade to deepen the hue.

9.text: Cover glossy reds with flat reds to change the texture of a wall.

10.text: Switch from oil to acrylic paint if you’re working on a canvas.
